== Accessing stickers ==
There are multiple ways to access stickers depending on the use case.

===Placing stickers===
Users can place stickers either by:
* Opening the [[Action Menu]], then navigating through <code>Emojis & Stickers</code> '''>''' <code>Stickers</code> '''>''' <code>"Default Stickers"</code> or <code>"Custom Stickers"</code>, then select a sticker.
* Using the wings on either the [[Main Menu]] or [[Quick Menu]], select <code>Stickers</code>, then select a sticker.
'''Note:''' Worlds can choose to disable stickers for their world. If a world has stickers disabled, the sticker placing UI will notify you with a "Stickers are disabled in this world" tooltip.

===Managing stickers===
Users can manage stickers either by:
* Opening the Quick Menu, select the VRC+ tab, and then select the <code>Stickers</code> button.
* Opening the Main Menu, select the <code>Inventory</code> tab, and then select the <code>Stickers</code> button.

== SDK ==
World creators have the option to disable stickers from being placed in the world, from their world page on the VRChat website; or disallow them from being placing on certain colliders, using layers in the [[VRChat SDK]]. 

''Learn more on the [https://creators.vrchat.com/worlds/layers/#stickers Creator Docs page].''

